description: Deletes an existing snapshot. When you receive a successful response from this operation, ElastiCache immediately begins deleting the snapshot; you cannot cancel or revert this operation.

parameters.name: SnapshotName
parameters.description: The name of the snapshot to be deleted.

nested_items.name: SnapshotName
nested_items.description: The name of a snapshot. For an automatic snapshot, the name is system-generated. For a manual snapshot, this is the user-provided name.

nested_items.name: ReplicationGroupId
nested_items.description: The unique identifier of the source replication group.

nested_items.name: ReplicationGroupDescription
nested_items.description: A description of the source replication group.

nested_items.name: CacheClusterId
nested_items.description: The user-supplied identifier of the source cluster.

nested_items.name: SnapshotStatus
nested_items.description: The status of the snapshot. Valid values: creating | available | restoring | copying | deleting.

nested_items.name: SnapshotSource
nested_items.description: Indicates whether the snapshot is from an automatic backup ( automated) or was created manually ( manual).

nested_items.name: CacheNodeType
nested_items.description: The name of the compute and memory capacity node type for the source cluster.

nested_items.name: M7g node types
nested_items.type: not recommended. Existing clusters are still supported but creation of new clusters is not supported for these types.
nested_items.description: General purpose:

nested_items.name: C1 node types:
nested_items.type: not recommended. Existing clusters are still supported but creation of new clusters is not supported for these types.
nested_items.description: Compute optimized:

nested_items.name: C1 node types:
nested_items.type: not recommended. Existing clusters are still supported but creation of new clusters is not supported for these types.

nested_items.name: R7g node types
nested_items.type: not recommended. Existing clusters are still supported but creation of new clusters is not supported for these types.
nested_items.description: Memory optimized:

nested_items.name: Engine
nested_items.description: The name of the cache engine ( memcached or redis) used by the source cluster.

nested_items.name: EngineVersion
nested_items.description: The version of the cache engine version that is used by the source cluster.

nested_items.name: NumCacheNodes
nested_items.description: The number of cache nodes in the source cluster.

nested_items.name: PreferredAvailabilityZone
nested_items.description: The name of the Availability Zone in which the source cluster is located.

nested_items.name: PreferredOutpostArn
nested_items.description: The ARN (Amazon Resource Name) of the preferred outpost.

nested_items.name: CacheClusterCreateTime
nested_items.description: The date and time when the source cluster was created.

nested_items.name: PreferredMaintenanceWindow
nested_items.description: Specifies the weekly time range during which maintenance on the cluster is performed. It is specified as a range in the format ddd:hh24:mi-ddd:hh24:mi (24H Clock UTC). The minimum maintenance window is a 60 minute period.
sun.
mon.
tue.
wed.
thu.
fri.
sat.

nested_items.name: TopicArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the topic used by the source cluster for publishing notifications.

nested_items.name: Port
nested_items.description: The port number used by each cache nodes in the source cluster.

nested_items.name: CacheParameterGroupName
nested_items.description: The cache parameter group that is associated with the source cluster.

nested_items.name: CacheSubnetGroupName
nested_items.description: The name of the cache subnet group associated with the source cluster.

nested_items.name: VpcId
nested_items.description: The Amazon Virtual Private Cloud identifier (VPC ID) of the cache subnet group for the source cluster.

nested_items.name: AutoMinorVersionUpgrade
nested_items.description: If you are running Valkey 7.2 and above or Redis OSS engine version 6.0 and above, set this parameter to yes if you want to opt-in to the next auto minor version upgrade campaign. This parameter is disabled for previous versions.

nested_items.name: SnapshotRetentionLimit
nested_items.description: For an automatic snapshot, the number of days for which ElastiCache retains the snapshot before deleting it.

nested_items.name: SnapshotWindow
nested_items.description: The daily time range during which ElastiCache takes daily snapshots of the source cluster.

nested_items.name: NumNodeGroups
nested_items.description: The number of node groups (shards) in this snapshot. When restoring from a snapshot, the number of node groups (shards) in the snapshot and in the restored replication group must be the same.

nested_items.name: AutomaticFailover
nested_items.description: Indicates the status of automatic failover for the source Valkey or Redis OSS replication group.

nested_items.name: NodeSnapshots
nested_items.description: A list of the cache nodes in the source cluster.

nested_items.name: CacheClusterId
nested_items.description: A unique identifier for the source cluster.

nested_items.name: NodeGroupId
nested_items.description: A unique identifier for the source node group (shard).

nested_items.name: CacheNodeId
nested_items.description: The cache node identifier for the node in the source cluster.

nested_items.name: NodeGroupConfiguration
nested_items.description: The configuration for the source node group (shard).

nested_items.name: NodeGroupId
nested_items.description: Either the ElastiCache supplied 4-digit id or a user supplied id for the node group these configuration values apply to.

nested_items.name: Slots
nested_items.description: A string that specifies the keyspace for a particular node group. Keyspaces range from 0 to 16,383. The string is in the format startkey-endkey.

nested_items.name: ReplicaCount
nested_items.description: The number of read replica nodes in this node group (shard).

nested_items.name: PrimaryAvailabilityZone
nested_items.description: The Availability Zone where the primary node of this node group (shard) is launched.

nested_items.name: ReplicaAvailabilityZones
nested_items.description: A list of Availability Zones to be used for the read replicas. The number of Availability Zones in this list must match the value of ReplicaCount or ReplicasPerNodeGroup if not specified.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: PrimaryOutpostArn
nested_items.description: The outpost ARN of the primary node.

nested_items.name: ReplicaOutpostArns
nested_items.description: The outpost ARN of the node replicas.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: CacheSize
nested_items.description: The size of the cache on the source cache node.

nested_items.name: CacheNodeCreateTime
nested_items.description: The date and time when the cache node was created in the source cluster.

nested_items.name: SnapshotCreateTime
nested_items.description: The date and time when the source node's metadata and cache data set was obtained for the snapshot.

nested_items.name: KmsKeyId
nested_items.description: The ID of the KMS key used to encrypt the snapshot.

nested_items.name: ARN
nested_items.description: The ARN (Amazon Resource Name) of the snapshot.

nested_items.name: DataTiering
nested_items.description: Enables data tiering. Data tiering is only supported for replication groups using the r6gd node type. This parameter must be set to true when using r6gd nodes. For more information, see Data tiering.
